<subSubSection id="52F9E3573DF352904AC917103738AF8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="type material">
<paragraph id="8D939708A12ADE6D8307C993456056D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D22CFDAA0F36A91B97D0D04B870B99E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="5F869D50C0DCF3C6A1E55931FD375723" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Holotype</emphasis>
, ♀, &quot;(JAPAN) Nagano Pref., Ueda City, Sugadaira-kougen, Tsukuba Univ., 36-31N/138-20E, about 1300 m alt., 13 IX 2013 (sweeping), Sou Shimizu leg.&quot; (OMNH). 
<emphasis id="B7F30836F1897FF6F0F80C956185B7F6" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Paratypes</emphasis>
: 1♀, 
<normalizedToken id="53FD2BC81B4B5C5469CD3BAE36DFBE9A" originalValue="Hokkaidô">Hokkaido</normalizedToken>
Pref., Sapporo City, Teine Ward, Mt. Teine, 18.IX.2013, S. Fujie leg. (OMNH); 1♀, Tochigi Pref., 
<normalizedToken id="DBD469F362BD08DE06BB7F02D8EF02B4" originalValue="Nikkô">Nikko</normalizedToken>
, 13.X.1986, M. Miyazaki leg. (NARO); 1♀, Nagano Pref., Shimashima-dani, 1300-1600 m alt., 26.VIII.1978, K. 
<normalizedToken id="38B05DA8AEE0564C2866DD274F0D0CEA" originalValue="Maetô">Maeto</normalizedToken>
leg. (NARO); 1♀, Tokushima Pref., Ichiu Vil., Mt. Tsurugi, 15.X.1980, Y. 
<normalizedToken id="82B6AA7C971DA9282F8620D6AE1AE2AE" originalValue="Shôno">Shono</normalizedToken>
leg. (NARO).
</paragraph>
<caption id="CEB6DBA7BB911F095BC010D93D9DBDDA" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669146" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
<paragraph id="1CC43B915EDC4E06C4A9062CFCED3706" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="97CB86DF83433E3369C1B9EA932D9A2E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Figure 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="758F656E841907C47FD8B0ADC5EED0DF" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipes">
<emphasis id="206B61387558658145135D735D3C8A8A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Papp, 1965, ♀ from Taiwan 
<emphasis id="6A6868F3863128689E3C040F019DF163" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">A</emphasis>
habitus 
<emphasis id="D800CE1FF01B4F59771F8048EEFBD27F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">B</emphasis>
head, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="1647BDBBBF0062AAE4329C176D9C36DB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">C</emphasis>
apical antennal segments.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58E880A52E1CBDB47187A70B6748A374" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="65E7C313A70B6B821DB0D41F0EEE01CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A0CF88370E917EE5E92FF3F8268B61D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
Named after its similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="ECC966FFFA06E847CF34A3F2FA7DBFBF" genus="A." lsidName="A. rutilipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="rutilipes">
<emphasis id="1C1A0F0D0AD14783803557D1F9DCBA2C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">A. rutilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Papp. The Latin suffix -
<normalizedToken id="59DCECF2F228B4E462BC8C489097B233" originalValue="“oides”">&quot;oides&quot;</normalizedToken>
taken from Greek means similar but not the same.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D7EC6DFD1973F69D54F2392905839EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="description">
<paragraph id="54AC9213B8555A904FB0AE629373423A" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0BAB64978A152D8240CCC9A1D933F113" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="6A89B2F8D5A983863C22FCA6F2BDBB20" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
Female 
<emphasis id="0481337DE616C1511486ECA57C728AAA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">holotype</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EFB5DE33BE1574B550C19C4731031BA7" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7</figureCitation>
). Body length 6.5 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC8725BB7F07E4EDA62180D8BF9480EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="D1060600AEF16A909A017A3F560DD682" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EDB25C60A6201B21E8E0E1FFB5C75E4" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7B, C, D, E</figureCitation>
). Width of head 2.0
<normalizedToken id="C5B80195DB68FB61A09D0311B579F774" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
median length and 1.1
<normalizedToken id="3FF22D50486AD7DC785087200543FF31" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
width of mesonotum. Length of eye 1.2
<normalizedToken id="12F9A057E911B27A82FA766969B3C646" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of temple in dorsal view. OOL / OD = 4.1. POL / OD = 1.7. Vertex and temple densely punctate. Occipital carina complete. Frons smooth and shining, with a distinct median carina. Face 1.9
<normalizedToken id="01E6D759EA84ADDE178264E8559CEBD2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as high; finely punctate laterally, transversely punctate-rugose medially. Intertentorial distance / tentorio-ocular distance = 1.7. Clypeus finely punctate, slightly concave medially, without apical teeth. Length of malar space 0.60
<normalizedToken id="21C270BE7A131C855986651133D4ED1C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye height. Malar suture indistinct. Antenna filiform with 18 segments; 3rd segment 3.5
<normalizedToken id="E7802637928C4FD0337C0EEB35432A35" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide and 1.2
<normalizedToken id="B176BCE2B3BCDEF003489C4D1F6F42AA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than 4th one; penultimate one 1.3
<normalizedToken id="7E1FE8B4A10F582F9FE3FF12CE2131EA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9357ECEF406D9AE0683283255CEE5229" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
<paragraph id="EFEA4609C3769277A22D6E9566F20B67" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="32A512F87C7608CCEB84DE865C9CB0B2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Figure 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BDF53DB1AE04820CFAF74E2A037AF0E6" authorityName="Fujie &amp; Maeto" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipoides">
<emphasis id="871509236DA607104E6B92F864D98CC7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., ♀ holotype 
<emphasis id="D07F4F7CD5CD559346A6F578BFDA57E6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">A</emphasis>
habitus 
<emphasis id="A344BAD956AE442ADB7727272420B7A8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">B</emphasis>
head, frontal view 
<emphasis id="B863738FEECE7B48A7647EF771825B05" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">C</emphasis>
head, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="4ED218634772F42D127E21CF19187D72" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">D</emphasis>
basal antennal segments 
<emphasis id="C28B60B73F855AEE734D31D8C9A28573" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">E</emphasis>
apical antennal segments 
<emphasis id="4858B5BFB54843D317A1419AFEB5CEE1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">F</emphasis>
mesosoma, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="AE4AE5C6F09C59741EF510177FAEC58D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">G</emphasis>
wings 
<emphasis id="7C7CB4D1EA977AC352B5E54BDCD3486D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">H</emphasis>
hind femur 
<emphasis id="DD245856CC74B477A7F994EBAA2C4604" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">I</emphasis>
first metasomal tergite, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E6033DDF84F73D7C3D6F6352D10442CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="38ADD6B940E122707788C6F4D21402A6" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8EDC31577E7402D42E99841DE90A696F" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7F</figureCitation>
). Mesosoma areolate, 1.3
<normalizedToken id="156A521229976B39E5C6EC321409331A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as high. Scutellum without median smooth area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="36CB800D6CA81702F2EBD622D6ECE1B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="E9D21C694258274130D5B8187F6FA0E0" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Wings</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A8178B1717CC7EB0033B6E7AD73B4C94" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7G</figureCitation>
). Fore wing 5.0 mm in length, 1-R1 / length of pterostigma = 1.3, r / 3-SR = 2.4, m-cu distinctly antefurcal. Hind wing with 1r-m / 2-SC+R = 0.8.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="655D85A0EC8C989E2138B71F55785221" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="5A4555041E242BA7D374F18BB0B9E920" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Legs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AB318732A069CE6EBCD866A8EE081832" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7H</figureCitation>
). Hind leg: femur 5.2
<normalizedToken id="A4EF26A148E2FF6727317511875CDC79" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, length of femur: tibia: basitarsus = 1: 1.3: 0.6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="77F02C8B909386D06C9F0EE83AF999BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="D77E014E0B8B0C52A02E99566A7F75F5" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Metasoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="79AC4065101D9CDAA31AE5F0A2DAD0BA" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7I</figureCitation>
). Metasoma smooth and polished. First metasomal tergite 5.9
<normalizedToken id="B2B9E0D2A567552FB49AEE8190E9129E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its apical width. Hypopygium truncated and excised apically. Ovipositor sheath hardly exserted beyond apex of metasoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8B3D889E7E39D57799432E4D4249591" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="AF9177F8FCB46615AC4475010B40DBE6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="F8C0E3CECFCC8D150D62B31B263E7339" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Colour</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Black. Antenna basally, mandible medially, palpi, tegula, legs except for telotarsus, metasoma reddish brown; mandible basally and apically, veins, telotarsus dark brown, antenna gradually darkened towards apex; pterostigma pale in basal quarter. Fore wing hyaline with two fuscous band. Hind wing with a fuscous band in apical third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE565A749DD170DA712B383C301AB71F" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="9B365D35C156EB247EC6EF841627E2FE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Variation in females.</emphasis>
Body length 5.8-6.5 mm. Length of eye 1.2-1.4
<normalizedToken id="55963BA98E81463630C19336C5286C29" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of temple in dorsal view; OOL / OD = 3.5-4.1. POL / OD = 1.5-1.9. Face 1.7-1.9
<normalizedToken id="D5099AC0212EF3B18B3F85B2282A5EB0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as high. Intertentorial distance / tentorio-ocular distance = 1.7-1.9. Length of malar space 0.5-0.6
<normalizedToken id="2E54888A280DB70B4B9893E57E731608" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye height. Malar suture indistinct or absent. Third antennal segment 3.5-4.0
<normalizedToken id="7F424F58A058F4F84E11651436312727" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide and 1.2-1.4
<normalizedToken id="02931BA78AD3877432DE88ADC5546846" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than 4th one; penultimate one 1.2-1.3
<normalizedToken id="1D3F88A4D4E9CF5B87773322926C1808" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide. Mesosoma length 1.3-1.4
<normalizedToken id="F6F2F20CB36F2283210654079F6125BE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
height. Fore wing 4.8-5.2 mm in length, 1-R1 / length of pterostigma = 1.2-1.5, r / 3-SR = 2.2-3.6. Hind wing with 1r-m / 2-SC+R = 0.8-1.0. Hind leg: femur 4.6-5.2
<normalizedToken id="3B6D68C4BDCD379F365516EB3669DD1A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, length of femur: tibia: basitarsus = 1: 1.3-1.4: 0.6. First metasomal tergite 5.9-6.3
<normalizedToken id="EDBDB1CB757E654186B1CEBBCAC86FD7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its apical width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99D4320E305EBE17EAB85A1AFEC2E2C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="3A4477102FAD38FF55276CD00D937F00" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="74772B0733C64620457A111CD3047AAB" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9ED2A1332CEF0F44A425FB86FDC5B9DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC8AF04F289AAB03A29C07B22670D00A" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
Japan (
<normalizedToken id="A9614969AB3005CA429BC1AA1841D844" originalValue="Hokkaidô">Hokkaido</normalizedToken>
; 
<normalizedToken id="48DFFEC15FE616217A4249E24D49579D" originalValue="Honshû">Honshu</normalizedToken>
: Nagano Prefecture; Shikoku: Tokushima Prefecture).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA6B8F2947FCD0E338CA509EB6B26597" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="host">
<paragraph id="6BF9FB8E88CC66DE3E8AC9C5FE87BBCD" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Hosts.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE177A50C25BD6DCAEEC34398371377D" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CF8D399586847F3CD254E8E376B44211" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C33460D64B343D79E3C117830901018D" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA92E4265E7C067644B7C815031D5FEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="DBFAB2344AFFF411FFE84050494C1C81" genus="A." lsidName="A. rutilipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="rutilipes">
<emphasis id="7B3242A1AC62BC147AAC22B9A4669AD4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">A. rutilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Papp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5959A6ABF969C60BBF574A3900C4F176" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Aridelus rutilipes Papp, 1965, ♀ from Taiwan A habitus B head, dorsal view C apical antennal segments." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669146" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">6</figureCitation>
) but differs in having the stouter penultimate antennal segment (in 
<taxonomicName id="0E1E0BAE94F7E46220AE6E63DD636368" authorityName="Fujie &amp; Maeto" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipoides">
<emphasis id="18D8CC5FFC7055EBF6483CA6E4AA0591" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 1.2-1.3
<normalizedToken id="AC5F5E2455F431778D1D457EB55A63AC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="64C151873174B181EF9A7621B84CF45E" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7E</figureCitation>
), in 
<taxonomicName id="956AEBDB3C0C56A907010C9FD8065B31" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipes">
<emphasis id="706C1F052711FF430F5E5D7B23B4EFAF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
1.8
<normalizedToken id="4644CAC382B260797527DE93E9FE2F21" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E289008E902413D6DEE9CE67CBE5FC3E" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Aridelus rutilipes Papp, 1965, ♀ from Taiwan A habitus B head, dorsal view C apical antennal segments." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669146" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">6C</figureCitation>
)), the face finely punctate laterally, transversely punctate-rugose medially (finely punctate in 
<taxonomicName id="8B692F653E70450026BC45258AF2DB38" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipes">
<emphasis id="FE2BAFF0160489A7890A26A23F3F128E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the apical hyaline area of the fore wing not reaching the apico-posterior edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C846E37A7A5CD29D5A7C8CC5FDD54E42" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7G</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4D945F1228CF33751AD87AB906BAD09C" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipes">
<emphasis id="940BD69688150298A160A50E05700D63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, reaching the apico-posterior edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A4C91113B1606F2037A31E0DC2CC220A" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Aridelus rutilipes Papp, 1965, ♀ from Taiwan A habitus B head, dorsal view C apical antennal segments." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669146" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">6A</figureCitation>
)) and the metasoma reddish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="99AF7FECA24A6109B5A0FAEF2383FCBD" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7A</figureCitation>
) (dark brown in 
<taxonomicName id="2E3D924A80DA33024A4C0B0A3BFD2C4C" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipes">
<emphasis id="9A8D19413AAA1DC57952489DD703E3CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0EBD5304D4166B6BD03A65682882C434" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Aridelus rutilipes Papp, 1965, ♀ from Taiwan A habitus B head, dorsal view C apical antennal segments." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669146" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">6A</figureCitation>
)). This species also resembles 
<taxonomicName id="39F860B69DDE4CAD4DBD81614E0418E1" genus="A." lsidName="A. dubius" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="A2FDFE3F527CD3915BC019458A20248A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">A. dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Belokobylskij, but differs in having the antenna gradually darkened towards the apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A3019C87EEF22BCB35C66D761745595" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7A</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="DDF37EFFAC139B311E33BEB72018C34C" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus dubius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="CAD897BFEE5D56EE0596D5B329EB828C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
uniformly reddish brown, not darkened towards the apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FC868B23EF0EF37B72278C9B05FD38CD" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Aridelus dubius Belokobylskij, 1981, ♀ from Niigata Prefecture, Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F wings G hind femur." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669141" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">1A</figureCitation>
)), the penultimate antennal segment stouter (in 
<taxonomicName id="D86E15F4AECD3E5775266C5B01D76C9F" authorityName="Fujie &amp; Maeto" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus rutilipoides" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rutilipoides">
<emphasis id="0B4B05DE13080D493855659864E199C8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus rutilipoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 1.2-1.3
<normalizedToken id="26DDDAA9F736CEB0CF8D4A460A741894" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0DF905F75841497071A69D5B655F785A" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7E</figureCitation>
), in 
<taxonomicName id="0FC39FB2D4FF6E19BFFAEC103D3236D9" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus dubius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="E09DB678788436F43531969547D600F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
1.6-1.7
<normalizedToken id="7BB04224A3825CFA33D33C31DAF63420" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0D1366B8B6FDE7AFBA33FB3B8546DE1D" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Aridelus dubius Belokobylskij, 1981, ♀ from Niigata Prefecture, Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F wings G hind femur." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669141" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">1E</figureCitation>
)), the face finely punctate laterally, transversely punctate-rugose medially (finely punctate in 
<taxonomicName id="81FF4D97A31B9C73E8A3D0BD730C303A" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus dubius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="72B50DC8F0D82DE222E4873511D8D9B0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the malar suture indistinct or absent (distinct in 
<taxonomicName id="3219B1859A8160528DBAE078DD13D965" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus dubius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="6552E390AB2B9246D8E5AB94ECE51CC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) the apical hyaline area of the fore wing comparatively large, almost reaching the apex of the marginal cell (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="07F6570DDA8DA3F4BCE8ADD990206281" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7G</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="76961A00159ED88BFF17FF0D90BD6312" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus dubius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="40A9C54B9F5B2B75302CC40128341A19" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comparatively small, not reaching the apex of the marginal cell (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="621611BA173EE8EACE3B3C96640C642C" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Aridelus dubius Belokobylskij, 1981, ♀ from Niigata Prefecture, Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F wings G hind femur." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669141" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">1F</figureCitation>
)), the vein m-cu of the fore wing antefurcal (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2A15E58CD45462697DBDF2E3E8710F14" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7G</figureCitation>
) (slightly postfurcal to interstitial in 
<taxonomicName id="9F114B05161D6B2949C596ACB2EDE70E" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus dubius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="C7E726F29FF766D938F0AB96D1699161" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C29C14FD363175CE8B6B77B9881E9A5B" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Aridelus dubius Belokobylskij, 1981, ♀ from Niigata Prefecture, Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F wings G hind femur." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669141" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">1F</figureCitation>
)), and the hind femur slenderer, 4.6-5.2 times as long as wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5C06B802B16A2F68790427856E4B4181" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Aridelus rutilipoides sp. nov., ♀ holotype A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F mesosoma, dorsal view G wings H hind femur I first metasomal tergite, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669147" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">7H</figureCitation>
) (4.1-4.3 times as long as wide in 
<taxonomicName id="626D01A7AB8B5373DCA8B15F0B21368C" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus dubius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="73E3FDB63C1D1C62123858134DFDD0C1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0207B32D6F5271BA46D1227C1B48471C" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Aridelus dubius Belokobylskij, 1981, ♀ from Niigata Prefecture, Japan A habitus B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D basal antennal segments E apical antennal segments F wings G hind femur." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.73299.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669141" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">1G</figureCitation>
)). This species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A511D59772DF9E34E0D46B277AFBE1A5" genus="A." lsidName="A. ussuriensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis id="CCA4CCDE61C71C85C9849877AE31C177" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">A. ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Belokobylskij, 1981 described from the Russian Far East, but differs in having the vertex densely punctate (vertex with distinct transverse striation in 
<taxonomicName id="853A0A4CBB26CCCC5D3D8429DE3520F9" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus ussuriensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis id="2393759912F1DBCBB687A23E20D4F208" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the mesosoma black (mesosoma red except for the prothorax black in 
<taxonomicName id="C28065802C099F2ABA7F05910C02F6AD" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus ussuriensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis id="2C1717B5BA0820DE4BA764EB8330334D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the metasoma entirely yellowish brown (metasoma black except for the red first metasomal tergite in 
<taxonomicName id="6C4C2A64370B05A7D93F9EF186D6B779" authorityName="Belokobylskij" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Aridelus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aridelus ussuriensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ussuriensis">
<emphasis id="9DE7E3F612CC958B57D6D0684F7E519F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Aridelus ussuriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
